# ===============================================================================================
# SECURITY CHECKLIST - BEFORE COMMITTING
# ===============================================================================================
# 1. ✓ Run 'git add -p' to review changes before staging
# 2. ✓ Use 'git add --intent-to-add' for sensitive files you want to track structure-only
# 3. ✓ Check 'git ls-files' for any accidentally added sensitive files
# 4. ✓ Never add .env files with real secrets
# 5. ✓ Review .gitignore regularly and update as needed
# 6. ✓ Use 'git secret' or similar tools for truly sensitive configuration
#
# REMEMBER: It's better to not track sensitive files at all than to accidentally commit them.
# If you did commit a secret, revoke it immediately and rotate to a new one.
# ===============================================================================================
